Package index

Datasets

The website “Making Maps with R” uses the datasets within this package. These datasets have a spatial/location component in that they can be located on a map. These objects are either of sf class or can be converted to it. sf is a package and abbreviation for “simple features.” It is the standard for encoding spatial vector data. While 18 geometry types are supported, only seven are used in practice: polygons, lines, points and their “multi” combinations.

Polygons

atlanta
Census data on the Atlanta MSA in 2020
life_exp
U.S. life expectancy by county 2019

Lines

blue_riband
Award for the fastest transatlantic crossing by ship 1838 - 1952
earhart
Global flight path and disappearance of Amelia Earhart 1937
flights
Flights of U.S. domestic airlines February 2011
white_shark
White shark tracking data near Guadulope Island 2015 - 2019

Points

homicides
Homicides in San Francisco 2018 - 2023
red_tide
Red tides in the Gulf of Mexico 1953 to 2023

Flows

bkshr_flows
Capital bikeshare rides September 2024
bkshr_sites
Capital bikeshare stations September 2024
dc_flows
Washington D.C. number of inbound commuters 2020
dc_sites
Washington D.C. commuter counties 2020
txpyr_flows
U.S. interstate taxpayer migration 2021 - 2022
txpyr_sites
U.S. interstate taxpayer states 2021 - 2022
